description:
I need a macro to be created in Excel that I click a button and it will transform the CSV file into a new CSV file with correct formatting. The button should be in the ribbon.
Attached is an example of how the Raw CSV file will look before the macro ran - &amp;quot;rawdata.csv&amp;quot;
After ran, it should look like the attached &amp;quot;output.csv&amp;quot;
The examples should be clear, but a few things to note.
1) You will need some lookups for country and shipping. Those are in the csv called &amp;quot;lookups.csv&amp;quot;
Please hardcode these into the macro.
2) Ignore items in column R of the raw data that DO NOT have - Snip Free Sample 
3) Column D of the output file is Column R from the raw data concatenated with like names (order numbers) separated with pipes &amp;quot;|&amp;quot; and removing the &amp;quot; - Snip Free Sample&amp;quot;
4) There can be instances of entire order #s that are not on the output since none of the items have the &amp;quot;- Snip Free Sample&amp;quot;&nbsp;&nbsp;For example #2495 would not be on the output<b>Skills</b>:        Microsoft Excel,                     Visual Basic for Applications,                     Macro Programming,                     Visual Basic,                     Spreadsheet Software
